# midiin: degenerate edge the manual leaves silent -- how many voices exist and
# what voiceallocation = 1 ("omit", line 340) does when they are all busy.
#
# CHOSEN READING (M3 convention, documented in circuits-status.yaml): the number
# of voices is the highest voice index for which ANY per-voice output
# (pitchN/gateN/velocityN/pressureN/triggerN) is patched. Here only pitch1/gate1
# are patched -> exactly ONE voice. With voiceallocation = 1, a second
# simultaneous note is dropped and the held note keeps its voice untouched;
# after the first note is released the voice is free for the next note.
patch <<<
[midiin]
    voiceallocation = 1
    pitch1 = O1
    gate1  = O2
>>>
@0 midisend trs noteon 1 60 100
@0 expect O2 1
@0 expect O1 0.3
@1 midisend trs noteon 1 64 100
@1 expect O2 1
@1 expect O1 0.3
@2 midisend trs noteoff 1 60 0
@2 expect O2 0
@3 midisend trs noteon 1 67 100
@3 expect O2 1
@3 expect O1 0.358333 tol 0.0001
